                    <msContents>
                        <summary>A guide to basic medical remedies in Japanese compiled on the orders of shogun Tokugawa Yoshimune, and published in 1729. The work was created by two doctors working for the Bakufu government; Hayashi Ryōteki, who was attached to the medical clinic established by the Bakufu for the poor, and Niwa Shōhaku, who was a herbalist and wrote a number of other works. </summary>

